			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like Wezloc's idea of a "helper" pet that buffs the mage, and perhaps only works as an enchanter-style pet otherwise.
<br />

<br />
However, having another DPS pet that trades even more "offtank ability" for "easier to use" DPS is fine by me.  Our other pets only differ by hp and procs, or by some singular special ability. (i.e. ...I forget whose idea this was... its simple and thats why I like it... it should do the DPS of water, but from any angle, and have a self DS to boot, for mana savings when hunting low blues -- at the expense of having the fewest hp and least mitigation of any pet, which is currently has)
<br />

<br />
To make the simple "DPS of water, but from any angle, while having fewer hp and mitigation" change:
<br />

<br />
(these ideas are summations of several already posted)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><span style="color: red">
<br />
* Change the class to berserker or warrior, but make sure it has the weapon skills to fully utilize the current mage weapons.
<br />
* Increase max melee damage to 83.  (L52 and L58 pets should be 58 and 70 damage respectively)  Have the focuses work as they currently do on the other pets.
<br />
* Keep the same hp and mitigation it has currently.
<br />
* Add a FireElementalStrike2 proc to it, which does 3x (as opposed to 2x) the pet level in damage, and set its cycle time to be the same as the WaterElementalStrike2 proc.  Make this proc a lure.
<br />
* Retain the fire pet DS.
<br />
</span></span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><span style="color: green">
<br />
...alternatively, keep the melee damage low, but change the class to warrior/berserker, make the proc be about 6-8x the pet level in damage, and don't make it a lure (the numbers are available here on the board to ensure that the proc damage + melee damage is near that of the water pet -- 6-8x is just a guess).  That way more of the damage dealing is coming from an unusual source, which is an interesting change.
<br />
</span></span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><span style="color: blue">
<br />
...as a third option, up the mana regen of Kindle, such that the fire pet can sustain a reasonable amount of damage without having to melee, rather than being reclaimed between fights.  As another alternate, change kindle to be a single tick, huge mana regen (say 800 mana, for a cost of ~200 to the mage, which is less efficient than the mage using it herself, since the pet has poorer ratio spells, does not benefit from spell focuses, etc.), which will effectively allow the mage to do better burst damage by excess mana expenditure over time.  In addition, the Root spell (and perhaps dispel) needs to be removed from the spell lineup.
<br />
</span></span>
<br />

<br />
All good ideas.  I was originally in favor of <span style="color: red">#1</span> or <span style="color: green">#2</span>, but the latter part of <span style="color: blue">#3</span> sounds kinda interesting, and was probably the intent of the wizzy pet all along -- though the original implementation is not very balanced.<br />_________________<br />Arhallia Ironborne
<br />
<span style="color: red">65th Arch Convoker</span>
<br />
Toenan Twosoks
<br />
<span style="color: green">57th Animist</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue"><span style="font-weight: bold">Alliance of the Arcane</span></span>
<br />
