				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We already have a tank pet and a high dps melee pet. What we need is a caster pet. All the other basses are covered. It's just been poorly implemented thus far.
<br />

<br />
 What I propose be done is that the fire pet since it has the least amount of hitpoints have a spell lineup consisting only of nukes, absolutley no debuffs or immoblization spells I.E. No cancel magic or root. The pet will have an unlimited mana pool, this is the only way the fire pet will work. Fixed mana pool will never work for a pet because of the inherint dis-advantage an npc is at versus a human caster. To make this not be overpowering, what Sony needs to do is when you send the fire pet to attack it gets within spell range but not too close. maybe 2-30 feet within range, and it begins casting nukes based on the mob's health. The fire pet will nuke at a fixed percentage until it hits that mark. When it does hit that mark it will stop nuking. So basically is the Fire pet will nuke for a certain amount of DPS scaleable of course through focus and when he reaches that potential # he shuts off.
<br />

<br />
As an example fire pet nukes a mob for 120 dps cap. once he hits the 120 dps cap unless the mob heals itself he stops. You calculate the 120 Dps by the spells potentional damage. So 120 dps worth of potentional spell damage. Now the fire pet may get interrupted or get resisted. That's the inherent drawback in the system but I think reasonable when other pet's can miss swings on high ac mobs.
<br />

<br />
The DPS cap needs to be just as high or a little bit higher then the water pet's and it needs to scale with focus. I truely think this is the best idea because it combines both ideas without having to worry about the "stupidity" inherent in npc's which makes the fire pet what it is today. And would address the pet being "too overpowered" with an endless mana pool that some people advocate. It would never get higher Dps then our other pet's, he would always be readabily available and he would scale properly with focuses like other pet's do.<br />_________________<br /><SELECT name=""> <OPTION selected>Azmeka Raidner's tradeskills and whatnots<OPTION>Resident of Stormhammer<OPTION>Guilded in Knights of Zek, <a href="http://www.Kozsh.org" target="_blank">www.Kozsh.org</a><OPTION>Grandmaster Smith (250) + Trophy<OPTION>Grandmaster Fletcher (250)<OPTION>Grandmaster Baker (250) + Trophy<OPTION>Grandmaster Brewer (250) + Trophy<OPTION>Grandmaster Tailor (250) + Trophy<OPTION>Grandmaster Potter (250)<OPTION>Grandmaster Jewler (250) + Trophy<OPTION>Grandmaster Fisherman (200)<OPTION>Completed Aid gimel and 8th shawl</OPTION></SELECT></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
